  • Method Details

    • run

      public java.lang.Object run​(java.util.List<java.lang.Object[]> target, java.lang.String key, java.lang.Class<?> clazz, java.lang.Object... args) throws java.lang.Throwable
      Called on every method call. This does the following: 1. Attempts to delegate to a verifier and exit using the default return value for this methods return type 2. Notifies the tracker 3. returns any callbacks (thenReturn/thenAnswer) that match this method/arg combination 4. returns the default return value for this methods return type
      Parameters:
      target - list to add data to - this should be a class member
      key - method name + description being called
      clazz - return type the method expects
      args - arguments passed to the method
      Returns:
      an instance of the expected return type, either taken from registered callbacks or the default fallback
      Throws:
      java.lang.Throwable - throws if either the callback or fallbacks throw

    • registerCallback

      public void registerCallback​(Visitor.Fn fn, java.lang.String key, java.util.function.Predicate<java.lang.Object>... args)
      Appends the given combination of parameters to the callbacks we will attempt to use when methods are called. Note that this replaces previous callbacks for this key. We do not append because it makes removing previous callbacks non-trivial (as the api doesn't currently return index info).
      Parameters:
      fn - callback to register
      key - method name + description we're targetting
      args - list of conditions for using this predicate

    • reset

      public void reset()
      Resets the current tracker and clears all callbacks Also resets the trackers call history. This should be used as often as possible as recorded history is unbounded and grows linearly with mock method calls

    • resetLast

      public static void resetLast()
      Resets the last called visitor. Used primarily for unit tests (see Mockery.reset())

    • rollbackLast

      public static <T> Mock<T> rollbackLast()
      Rollbacks the last called visitors entry, and returns a Mock capturing it
      Type Parameters:
      T - return type of the last entries output
      Returns:
      A mock describing the last method call seen
